The paper presents a fully-automatic framework for segmentation of the spinal cord and intramedullary MS lesions from MRI data using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN). Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the use of CNNs suggests that it may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which could place it in the Multimedia (cs.MM) category.
